      "writtenOn": "2017-04-03T19:33:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: I think this function will be simpler if you only look at t.Revision and ignore t.Commits, since there will always be gaps when using t.Commits. You would need to change the loop below to iterate backwards over commits. Essentially, this would adjust blamelists as if pending/running/mishap tasks had never been created.\n\nDoing this would eliminate the special wildcard handling, and also eliminate the fix-ups after makeSlice(t.Commits, commits).",
